---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="How to use" description="How to consume compliance-atoms in your application.">
  <h1>How to use compliance-atoms</h1>

  <h2>Read the catalog over HTTPS</h2>
  <p>Every artifact is served under stable URLs with correct content-types:</p>
  <pre><code>curl https://compliance-atoms.com/exports/catalog.json
curl https://compliance-atoms.com/atoms/control-family/access-control.json
curl https://compliance-atoms.com/frameworks/soc2-type2.json
curl https://compliance-atoms.com/schemas/composition-v1.json</code></pre>

  <h2>Resolve a compliance framework</h2>
  <p>A framework composition lists references to atoms by URI and version. To instantiate the framework,
  fetch each referenced atom and assemble: control families → controls → evidence types → audit requirements.</p>

  <pre><code>{`// pseudo-code
const composition = await fetch("/frameworks/soc2-type2.json").then(r => r.json());
const refs = composition.references;
const controlFamilies = await Promise.all(
  (refs.control_families ?? []).map(r => fetch(uriToUrl(r.ref)).then(r => r.json()))
);
const evidenceTypes = await Promise.all(
  (refs.evidence_types ?? []).map(r => fetch(uriToUrl(r.ref)).then(r => r.json()))
);
const framework = compileFramework({ controlFamilies, evidenceTypes });`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Cross-framework equivalence rules</h2>
  <p>Rules in <a href="/exports/catalog.json"><code>/exports/catalog.json</code></a> (under the <code>rules</code>
  key) declare cross-framework equivalences. Example: a SOC2 <code>CC6.1</code> control maps equivalently to
  ISO 27001 <code>A.9.1.1</code>. These equivalences let you satisfy multiple frameworks from a single
  control implementation.</p>

  <h2>Automation and evidence collection</h2>
  <p>v0.1 ships the catalog and its JSON Schema; evidence collectors for specific platforms
  (AWS, GCP, Azure, GitHub) are v0.2 work — they bind <code>evidence-type</code> atoms to platform
  APIs that produce the required evidence automatically.</p>
</Base>
